title: AIAA UIC
text: We Would Love to Hear From You
Our Organization Consists Primarily of Three Branches
We design, build, and fly unmanned aircrafts for competitions. Our team is divided into four subgroups: Aerodynamics, Design, Proptronics, and Structures.
We design and make quadcopters for competitions then watch our creations go head to head against other schools and see which one them was better designed!
We make rockets not only for fun but also for competitions that we travel the country to participate!
If you have any questions or need more information about the club, contact us via the form below. We look forward to hearing from you!

The AIAA (American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics) chapter at the University of Illinois at Chicago is a student run organization located in Region III. It is primarily dedicated to the study of aerospace and propulsion engineering.
